Detailed Description

cvmx_l2c_err_xmc

L2C_ERR_XMC = L2C XMC request error

Description: records error information for HOLE*, BIG* and VRT* interrupts.

Notes: (1) The first BIGWR/HOLEWR/VRT* interrupt will lock the register until L2C_INT_REG[6:1] are cleared.

(2) ADDR<15:0> will always be zero for VRT* interrupts.

(3) ADDR is the 38-bit OCTEON physical address after hole removal. (The hole is between DR0 and DR1. Remove the hole by subtracting 256MB from all 38-bit OCTEON L2/DRAM physical addresses >= 512 MB.)

(4) For 63xx pass 2.0 and all 68xx ADDR<15:0> will ALWAYS be zero.
